ccre.util

Class CAbstractList<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ccre.util.CAbstractList<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the element type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    CCollection<T>, CList<T>, java.lang.Iterable<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CArrayList, CLinkedList

    public abstract class CAbstractList<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements CList<T>
    An abstract list. This is the superclass of the list implementations in this package.

      • fillArray

        public int fillArray(java.lang.Object[] target)
        Description copied from interface: CCollection
        Fills the specified array with elements from this collection, and then returns how many elements didn't fit in the array. This is different than toArray because it will not reallocate the specified array if it is too short, just return a positive number. This exists instead of the more useful toArray because Squawk doesn't provide an easy way to create a new array of a given type.
        Specified by:
        fillArray in interface CCollection<T>
        Parameters:
        target - The array to fill.
        Returns:
        The size of the collection minus the length of the given array. This will be zero if the array was the perfect size, negative if the array was too long, and positive if the array was too short.
